description.narrative: Measles supplementary immunization activities (SIAs) took place in three countries (Kiribati, Solomon Islands, FSM (Chuuk State)), vaccinating more than 128,000 children. Newborn care action plans were developed in Kiribati, Solomon Islands and Vanuatu, building the capacity of 188 PHC workers on EENC. To address high rates of stunting and anaemia, 176 PHC workers in Kiribati, Solomon Islands and Vanuatu were trained on country-specific HINI. PHC workers in 69 health facilities across six provinces/districts in Solomon Islands, Vanuatu, and Kiribati benefited from PHC supportive supervision and on-the-job training. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
